glosses: To hang down by holding on to something.
To persistently ask for something so as to make the person uneasy; to importune someone.
To exert oneself, to give one's all.
To make unwanted sexual advances in an irritating way.

etymology: From Ottoman Turkish آصلمق (aṣılmaḳ, “to be hung, to be suspended, to hang, to cling”), from Ottoman Turkish آصمق (aṣmaḳ, “to hang up, to suspend”), from Proto-Turkic *as- (“to hang”), morphologically as- + -ıl- + -mak.
